# Sheets Push & Telegram

## sheets_push.py

- **Default: --safe** — Targeted ranges only; no full sheet clears. Preserve row 1 (meta), header row, formulas (W:AD VLOOKUPs), PlayerBlock S, tier colors.
- **Ranges**: Legs A2:Q{rows}, Cards A2:V{rows} + AE2:AJ{rows}, Tiers A2:AA{rows}. Bankroll log tab (if any): append-only, never clear.
- **--no-safe**: Legacy full data-range clear (use only when intentionally replacing all data).
- When safe and TTY: confirm before clear; when non-interactive (e.g. from run_optimizer), no prompt.

## Telegram

- **TELEGRAM_SHEET_URL** (optional in .env): Link included in Cards/UD messages.
- **Alerts**: sendTelegramAlert() on sheets push failure, low cards (<100), quota issues.
- UD message: Cards count, EV Top, sheet link. PP innovative: EV Top, sheet link in footer.

## Scheduler / 6PM

- **run-both.ps1** and **daily-run.ps1** pass **--no-require-alt-lines** so SGO quota/alt-lines errors don’t hard-fail.
- Cron/Netlify: include `--no-require-alt-lines` in the generate command. See docs/SCHEDULED_AUTOMATION.md for 6PM failure checks.

## Test

- `npm run generate -- --platform both --bankroll 600 --safe --debug`
